  "snippets": [
    {
      "text": "e show that the heart regulates systemic energy homeostasis via MED13, a subunit of the Mediator complex, which controls transcription by thyroid hormone and other nuclear hormone receptors. MED13, in turn, is negatively regulated by a heart-specific microRNA, miR-208a.",
      "document": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22541436",
      "beginSection": "sections.0",
      "endSection": "sections.0"
    },
    {
      "text": "On the other hand, T\u2083 treatment increased miR-350 expression.",
      "document": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22525353",
      "beginSection": "sections.0",
      "endSection": "sections.0"
    },
    {
      "text": "Through a bioinformatics screening using TargetScan, we identified thyroid hormone receptor \u03b21 (TR\u03b21), which negatively regulates \u03b2-MHC transcription, as a target of miR-27a",
      "document": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21149577",
      "beginSection": "sections.0",
      "endSection": "sections.0"
    },
    {
      "text": "hese findings suggested that miR-27a regulates \u03b2-MHC gene expression by targeting TR\u03b21 in cardiomyocytes.",
      "document": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21149577",
      "beginSection": "sections.0",
      "endSection": "sections.0"
    },
    {
      "text": "We found that a cardiac-specific microRNA (miR-208) encoded by an intron of the alphaMHC gene is required for cardiomyocyte hypertrophy, fibrosis, and expression of betaMHC in response to stress and hypothyroidism.",
      "document": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17379774",
      "beginSection": "sections.0",
      "endSection": "sections.0"
    },
    {
      "text": "Moreover, miR-27a was demonstrated to modulate \u03b2-MHC gene regulation via thyroid hormone signaling and to be upregulated during the differentiation of mouse embryonic stem (ES) cells or in hypertrophic hearts in association with \u03b2-MHC gene upregulation.",
      "document": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21149577",
      "beginSection": "sections.0",
      "endSection": "sections.0"
    }
